---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="EMC Compliance" description="EMC compliance testing and consultancy services. In-house pre-compliance testing for IEC 61000-4 standards. Fix EMC problems and achieve certification for EU markets.">
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="reveal text-4xl font-bold text-navy mb-8">EMC Compliance</h1>

      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy mb-4">
          With the proliferation of high-speed digital circuitry, high-current switchmode power supplies and various forms of wireless connectivity, electromagnetic problems are now abundant for poorly designed PCBs.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy mb-4">
          ntronIQ design each PCB to achieve the best EMC performance. Preventing various forms of interference, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-navy mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-pink mr-3">&#8226;</span> Electromagnetic Interference (EMI)</li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-pink mr-3">&#8226;</span> Conducted Emissions</li>
          <li class="flex items-center"><span class="text-pink mr-3">&#8226;</span> Electromagnetic susceptibility (EMS)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy mb-4">
          ntronIQ provide the requisite testing for compliance - ensuring the correct certification is in place for each region where the product is to be sold.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy">
          We also offer a consultancy service to track down and fix existing EMC problems.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal mt-12">
        <img
          src="/images/EMC.png"
          alt="EMC Testing"
          class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-lg"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
